  "articleSummary": "The articleargues that `transformers.js` has been silently falling back to greedy decoding because its `num_beams` parameter was never actually supported, and it walks the reader through a full implementation of true beam search—including standard, diverse, and sampling variants—to bring the library up to parity with the Python transformers reference. It explains the core technical challenges (ranking `num_beams × vocab_size` candidates, correctly reordering the KV‑cache after pruning, and managing completed hypotheses with a priority queue) and shows how the author solved them by computing log‑softmax directly, adding a cache‑reordering routine for both CPU and GPU tensors, and structuring diverse beam search as a sequential group process. The piece is written as a hands‑on tutorial aimed at JavaScript developers familiar with transformer models, using a light‑hearted “beam‑search as a bounded breadth‑first search” metaphor throughout.",
